Psalm 47

2 All péoples, cláp your hánds.
Cry to Gód with shóuts of jóy!
3 For the Lórd, the Most Hígh, is áwesome,
the great kíng over áll the éarth.

4 He húmbles péoples únder us
and nátions únder our féet.
5 Our héritage he chóse for ús,
the príde of Jácob whom he lóves.

6 God goes úp with shóuts of jóy.
The Lord goes úp with trúmpet blást.
7 Sing práise for Gód; sing práise!
Sing práise to our kíng; sing práise!

8 God is kíng of áll the éarth.
Sing práise with áll your skíll.
9 Gód reigns óver the nátions. 
God síts upon his hóly thróne.

10 The prínces of the péoples are assémbled
with the péople of the Gód of Ábraham.
The rúlers of the éarth belong to Gód,
whó is gréatly exálted.
